parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake master cylinder can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The rear brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the rear brake pedal sticks to the floor
the rear brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the rear brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the rear brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or slows down unexpectedly
burning smell
and high brake temperature.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front brake master cylinder can cause the brakes to wear out prematurely, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The front brake pads wear out prematurely
the front brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the front brake pedal sticks to the floor
the front brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the front brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the front brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to stop or slows down unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The brakes feel soft or spongy
the brakes stick to the floor
the brakes do not return to their normal position
the brakes have a delayed return to their normal position
the brakes have a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or slows down unexpectedly
and burning smell.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and shifting issues can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or stranding the rider on the highway.
symptoms: The transmission slips out of gear
the transmission shifts gears independently
the clutch makes a rattling sound when out of gear
the transmission tries to slip back out of gear when shifted back into gear
unexpected engine RPM changes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deceleration wobble can cause the motorcycle to become unstable, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The handlebars shake or wobble violently upon deceleration
typically between 35-45 mph
requiring both hands to be kept on the handlebars to avoid a crash
and the wobble increases if one hand is let go. The wobble can also cause discomfort
especially when going around corners
and may contribute to increased wear on the front tire and damage to other components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overheating of the handlebar grips can cause discomfort and potentially lead to loss of control, as the rider may be unable to maintain a secure grip on the handlebars.
symptoms: The handlebar grips become extremely hot
making it difficult or impossible to continue driving.
